title: FHA's Neighborhood Watch, Mortgage defaults by Zipcode in the Santa Ana region, USA, Oct 31, 2008
name: FHA's Neighborhood Watch, Mortgage defaults by Zipcode in the Santa Ana region, USA, Oct 31, 2008
description:
The poly shapefile shows at the zipcode level the number of defaults and claims on the FHA insured mortgages between Nov 2006 and Oct 2008 for the Santa Ana region. Note that Denver region consists of all the states in the Western states. Neighborhood watch is an early warning system instituted by FHA to get information on foreclosures on the loans insured by FHA. Here is information posted on the HUD
http://www.hud.gov/offices/hsg/sfh/lender/nw_home.cfm
Note that FHA has four major regions covering all the 50 states, DC and territories. They are Atlanta, Denver, Philadelphia and Santa Ana.
You can find data on other regions by searching with key word Housing or FHA

author.source: FHA (Federal Housing Adminstrations) Neighborhood Watch Website
